# The SHARED genet-probe scenario driver, driving the real merecat Shell through
# its Automatable/Driveable impl — proof that merecat and the shared driver are
# one loop, not two. Generic verbs only (act / click by selector / assert snap /
# assert text / assert event / capture); merecat's app-specific verbs are the
# coordinated follow-on behind Driveable::app_step. FRESH profile; no network.
settle 30
# `key escape` is an app-specific verb: the generic grammar does not know it, so
# the loop passes it to Driveable::app_step, which closes the fresh-run omnibar.
# This is the app_step seam working — an app verb flowing through the shared loop.
key escape
settle 3

# Open the Roster pane — a palette command, run through Automatable::act.
act Open Roster pane
settle 5
assert snap panes ~ roster
assert text Node
capture 01_shared_roster

# Click the Links tab by selector, resolved over the surfaces and pressed through
# Automatable — the same shared path every genet app inherits.
click .tab Links
settle 5
assert snap roster-tab == Links
capture 02_shared_tab

# A miss attributes itself into the event stream, so a scenario can assert it —
# the "loud AND attributable" rule, now a property of the shared loop itself.
click .tab NoSuchTab
settle 3
assert event interaction-missed .tab 'NoSuchTab'
log shared driver drives the real Shell — one loop
